k between ancient traditions and the modern Games.\", \"from\": 4690, \"to\": 4869, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4775, \"end\": 4780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.999271019740276, \"rank\": 0.0007288152256132505, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The lighting ceremony\", \"from\": 4690, \"to\": 4711}, {\"ngram\": \"the Temple\", \"from\": 4721, \"to\": 4731}, {\"ngram\": \"Hera\", \"from\": 4735, \"to\": 4739}, {\"ngram\": \"homage\", \"from\": 4746, \"to\": 4752}, {\"ngram\": \"the profound link\", \"from\": 4803, \"to\": 4820}, {\"ngram\": \"ancient traditions\", \"from\": 4829, \"to\": 4847}, {\"ngram\": \"the modern Games\", \"from\": 4852, \"to\": 4868}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The flame was kindled by the high priestess and, along with an olive branch symbolising peace, was passed to the first torchbearer.\", \"from\": 4870, \"to\": 5001, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The flame\", \"from\": 4870, \"to\": 4879}, {\"ngram\": \"the high priestess\", \"from\": 4895, \"to\": 4913}, {\"ngram\": \"an olive branch\", \"from\": 4930, \"to\": 4945}, {\"ngram\": \"peace\", \"from\": 4958, \"to\": 4963}, {\"ngram\": \"the first torchbearer\", \"from\": 4979, \"to\": 5000}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This honour was given toGreek rower, Tokyo 2020 Olympic gold medallist Stefanos Douskos, who then passed it on toLaure Manaudou, the first French torchbearer on Greek soil and an Olympic champion at Athens 2004.\", \"from\": 5003, \"to\": 5214, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5142, \"end\": 5148, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.4377142108936114, \"rank\": 0.7661840905985186, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 51